Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pop the @butternut squash{300%g}(diced) onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the
@chilli flakes{1%pinch}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{18-20%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, boil a full #kettle{}.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} stems lengthways.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Couscous ==

Put the @couscous{120%g} in a #bowl{}.

Pour the @boiled water{} from the kettle into the bowl.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, then cover tightly with #cling film{}.

Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Garlic Broccoli and Lemon Yoghurt ==

When the butternut has 10 mins left, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in medium #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add the garlic.
Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add a splash of @water{}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan, or cover in #foil{}, and cook until tender, a further
~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix together the lemon zest and @Greek style natural
yoghurt{75%g}. Season to taste.

== Zhoug Couscous ==

Fluff up the cooked couscous with a #fork{}.

Stir through the @Zhoug style paste{50%g}, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of
@olive oil{}.

Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

== To Serve ==

When ready, share the zhoug couscous between your #bowls{}.

Top with the roasted butternut squash and garlic broccoli, then crumble over the
@Greek style salad cheese{50%g}.

Add a dollop of lemon yoghurt and sprinkle over the remaining chilli flakes to
finish. Enjoy!